title: Christine Lagarde | Biography, IMF, ECB, & Facts | Britannica
snippet: Christine Lagarde (born January 1, 1956, Paris, France) is a French lawyer and politician who was the first woman to serve as France’s finance minister (2007–11), as the managing director of the International Monetary Fund (IMF; 2011–19), and as president of the European Central Bank (2019– ).

title: Christine Lagarde - European Central Bank
snippet: Christine Lagarde's is a career marked by firsts: first female chairman of a major international law firm, first woman to serve as French Finance and Economy Minister, and first woman to hold that position in any G7 country.
